latestIgtvVideos.title: Covid Era Makeup : What to expect .
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A must watch for every makeup&hair artist and anyone looking to book a makeup artist during Covid era . 
Answering questions such as :
1) Why does spraying IPA on your makeup doesn’t work and is a myth. 
2) Why is 70% concentrated IPA better than 99.9%
3) How to safely return back to work
4) How to reduce risk of contamination 
5) Why you might want to consider not carrying eye and eyebrow pencils  to work anymore 
6) Where to buy Disposables 
7) How to store your grips and pins 
8) Why getting rid of your Kit Bag is a good idea . 
9) Why you must consider taking bridal clients instead of backstage for the time being . 
10) How to convert your eyebrow powder in a brow pomade like texture . 
Please excuse my poor editing skills 😆

latestPosts.caption:
It’s always exciting when a bride dares to be different on her big day! Shirin embraced an out-of-the-box look with sleek pulled-back hair, a sultry smoky eye, glass skin, and an editorial finish—pure model glam.

The truth is, there’s no such thing as “bridal makeup.” What makes a look bridal is the outfit, jewelry, and veil, not just the makeup itself.

Thank you, Shirin, for trusting me as your makeup artist! It was an absolute pleasure working with you. Wishing you and your partner a lifetime of love and happiness! ❤️ 
Outfit @taruntahiliani

latestPosts.caption: Absolutely loved doing makeup on my mom — there’s something so special about it. When working with mature skin, here are a few key things to keep in mind: hydrate generously, opt for cream products for both face and eyes, stick to softer pinks and browns, and go for matte finishes with just a hint of shimmer rather than heavy glitters. A full tutorial is on the way — stay tuned!
